value: The sailfish fountain in the middle of the sailfish capital of the worlds down town is simply breathtaking, especially by night.
Stuart's house of refuge is the last one standing on the east Floridian coast, and is quite a neat story.

This downtown is truly amazing. It has shopping and great restaurants and is a treat for the whole family.

The Stuart, Bathtub, and Jensen beaches are very nice and truly a wonderful relaxing place to be. Look for small sea life (espcially at Bathtub beach at low tide) and relax. Don't forget your boogie boards or surf boards! You will want them.
Causeway park is a wonderful fishing place over the bridge in Jensen Beach. It is fun, has a small playground and facilities.
Across the bridge, downtown Jensen offers tons of fun in the hip, artsy little town.

A short drive away in Hobe Sound, this breath-taking river offers kayaking and other boating. While you're here, see and learn about the man who started this park, and lived alone out there for 50 years.
